The machines offer a selection of caviar<ref>[http://www.laweekly.com/restaurants/beverly-hills-caviar-vending-machine-caviar-escargot-and-bottarga-as-mall-food-2381380 "Beverly Hills Caviar: Vending Machine Caviar + Escargot and Bottarga as Mall Food"]. ''LA Weekly'', By Emily Dwass November 27, 2012</ref> in different sizes ranging from 40 grams (1.5 ounces) to 400 grams (a little less than a pound). The machine was built in Spain.<ref name="WJLA">{{cite news|url=http://www.wjla.com/articles/2012/11/caviar-vending-machine-unveiled-in-beverly-hills-82605.html|title=Caviar vending machine unveiled in Beverly Hills|date=November 30, 2012|publisher=ABC News / WJLA.com|accessdate=29 March 2014}}</ref> The machine holds about $50,000 worth of temperature-controlled merchandise.<ref name="CNN">{{cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/video/news/2012/11/29/n-caviar-vending-machine.cnnmoney/index.html|title=$500 caviar from a vending machine - Video - Business News|publisher=[[CNN]]|accessdate=29 March 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://www.wired.com/2014/05/self-servers-cool-snack-bots/ "These Snack Bots Serve You Cupcakes and Caviar Anytime"]. ''Wired''. Elise Craig, May 9, 2014</ref> After being dispensed, the product takes about 30 minutes to thaw.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gma.yahoo.com/blogs/abc-blogs/caviar-vending-machines-unveiled-california-malls-215644283--abc-news-Recipes.html|title=Caviar Vending Machines Unveiled at California Malls|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=29 March 2014}}</ref>
