'''''Interavia''''' was a Swiss monthly magazine on [[aerospace]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Aviation Magazines in Switzerland|url=http://www.aeroflight.co.uk/mags/mags-country/aviation-magazines-in-switzerland.htm|work=Aeroflight|accessdate=25 December 2014}}</ref> published in English, [[French language|French]], [[German language|German]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]] between 1946 and 1993: {{ISSN|0020-5168}}.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.pionnair-ge.com/spip1/spip.php?article365|title= Interavia: firme genevoise au magazine aéronautique de qualité, un impact planétaire de 60 ans (1946)|date=1 February 2010|work= Pionnair-GE|language= fr}}</ref>
In September 1992, Interavia was the leader of the aerospace press with a [[magazine circulation]] of 42,602 as French press group [[:fr:Le Revenu]] bought it from [[Jane's Information Group]], a [[Thomson Corporation]] subsidiary at the time.<!--<ref name=LesEchos2sep1992>--> It was to merge by October with monthly [[Aerospace World]] (circulation: 31,500) as ''Le Revenu'' also published [[Air & Cosmos]] (41,509) and [[Aéronautique et Astronautique]] (6,000), controlling 30% of the aerospace publications market with a [[₣]]300 millions revenue.<ref name=LesEchos2sep1992>{{cite news |url= https://www.lesechos.fr/02/09/1992/LesEchos/16214-085-ECH_le-revenu-francais-rachete---interavia-aerospace--.htm |title= Le Revenu Français rachète « Interavia Aerospace » |newspaper= Les Echos |date= 2 Sep 1992 |language= french}}</ref>
